	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Semi-Microphone support via Powerpak?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi, I was just wondering if it would be difficult or not to use the select button on NES controller 2 to act as a Famicom microphone.  I think that the Famicom microphone only registered sound in general and not different volumes, but I could be wrong.  What I mean is if you wanted to use the "microphone", you would just press select on controller 2 and it would register an input for the microphone.  That way people could get past Pol's Voice in Zelda and haggle in Kid Icarus for the FDS versions.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
