	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The Famicom mic is actually on controller port 1's register, and I seem to remember it's on D1 or D2, bits that are connected only to the expansion port, not the controller port. Of course, you could ROM-hack the game to get it to read player 2 select.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
